definition:
Someone descended from Nemuel who was a man of the tribe of Simeon living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.10; 
 son of: Simeon (H8095); 
 brother of: Jamin (H3226), Ohad (H0161), Jachin (H3199), Zerah (H2226L) and Shaul (H7586H); also called Nemuel at Num.26.12; 1x
Group of ye.mu.el (יְמוּאֵל "Jemuel" H3223) 
 § Nemuelites, of Nemuel "day of God"
 a descendant of Nemuel
